  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">ITER Core CXRS diagnostic: Assessment of different optical designs with respect to neutronics criteria</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2017-03-19</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The Charge Exchange Recombination Spectroscopy (CXRS) diagnostic aims to measure emission lines of impurity isotopes in the ITER plasma in order to quantify several parameters like the composition of the plasma (density of helium, deuterium or tritium), the ion temperature or rotation velocities. The core plasma CXRS shall be installed in one of the ITER Upper Port Plugs (UPP #3). Currently, four different optical layouts are being assessed with respect to the optical performance, engineering feasibility, cost, maintenance especially with respect to remote handling and the performance of their neutron radiation shielding.</subfield>
